            <title>[LU-8972] conf-sanity test_101: File hasn&apos;t object on OST</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8972</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/57cc8712-c9db-11e6-af18-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/57cc8712-c9db-11e6-af18-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_101 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;File hasn&apos;t object on OST

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: conf-sanity 101&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is quite new issue which starts to happen since yesterday, it can be related to some recent commits.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
